title: __init__
overview: Constructor for the Queue data structure.

title: __str__
overview: Returns a string representation of the Queue to display.

title: __repr__
overview: Returns a string representation of the Queue to debug.

title: limit
overview: Sets the Queue's Node object limit.
description: Raises ValueError if value is smaller than the Linked List's size.

title: enqueue
overview: Inserts new data in the Queue.
description: Raises ValueError if data is None.
Raises IndexError if Queue is full.

title: dequeue
overview: Removes and returns the first item in the Queue.
description: Raises IndexError if Queue is empty.

title: peek
overview: Returns the first item in the Queue without removing it.
description: Raises IndexError if Queue is empty.

title: contains
overview: Returns whether the data is in the Queue.
description: Raises ValueError if data is None.
Raises IndexError if Queue is empty.
Returns True if item is in the Queue.
Returns False if item is not in the Queue.

title: is_empty
overview: Returns whether the Queue is empty.
description: Returns True if Queue is empty.
Returns False if Queue is not empty.
